  id: 2_Markers
  headerName: TRAIL MARKERS
  content: "(A scrap of paper pinned to a wooden post)\n\nTo the Saturday Hikers:\r\nSarah
    and I cleared the brush on the East Path. The wild berries are coming in early!
    Please leave some for the bears, but definitely grab a handful near the Tall
    Pines. The shade there is the best on the mountain\u2014perfect for a midpoint
    rest.\r\n\r\nP.S. Isn\u2019t the air sweet today? Like pine and honey. We are
    so lucky to call this place home.\n\n"
  type: 0
  icon: {fileID: 0}
  dialogData: {fileID: 0}
